Thank you <@U01QVR44MEY>! I've solved the problem with a `setInterval()` to check the elements until existing on the code.

```const checker = setInterval(() =&gt; {
	const employeesSelector = document.getElementsByName("onboarding_number_employees_new")[0];
	const onboardingNumberEmployees = document.getElementsByName("onboarding_number_employees")[0];

	if(!!employeesSelector &amp;&amp; !!onboardingNumberEmployees) {
		clearInterval(checker)
		employeesSelector.addEventListener("change", function() {
		  var numberEmployees = employeesSelector.value;
		  onboardingNumberEmployees.value = numberEmployees;
		});
	}
}, 100)```
